Unfortunately, i didn't have inspiration source for my studies choice because i'm not in the study that i wanted to do.
When i was in high-school, i didn't know what to choose in Parcoursup, so I decided to choose study Sociology in Rennes 2. I wanted to study sociology because to me, it's very interessant to know why people do what they do, and particulary why societies are how they are, why they're not the same in differents countries, why they're is inegality and differences between men and women, why racism exists, why some people become dangerous... Sociology can respond at many questions of humans life, she get involved with history, geography, philosophy, psychology... It's amazing! I studied it in high-school and I realy liked.  My 'wish' on the site was accepted, but I inadvertenly deleted it (it's a little bit funny but a little bit sad to ahaha).
So now, I'm in Infocom, and i have a bit of sociology, but not much and the rest of things don't realy interest me, so I have nothing to say about it. Anyway, it's also interesting because I think I like journalism, and this studies can help, but I don't know. If I need to describe why I'm a little bit inspired in journalism, I think it's because it touches everythings, and I particulary like the fact to know actuality and writing about things we like. Also, in journalism, we can denounced many things. I also like everything related to beautiful pictures, audiovisual etc... and we can find it in journalism studies.
